WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Labyx' is a Workbench game where the goal is to get to the
exit, located somewhere on the edge of the game board, in the
least amount of moves possible. One way to accomplish this is the
"longer" method, which is to move about in the traditional way,
in the labyrinth.

  However, there is a "shorter" (simpler?) way to complete the
game: you can pivot, by 90 degres in a clockwise manner, the 8
tiles and empty spaces that surround your position, but if one or
more "riveted" tiles (tiles that have two small dots on them) are
among those 8 surrounding tiles, they will not rotate.

  Your starting position is in the middle of the 59 by 59 spaces
labyrinth, but to complicate matters, only a small portion (a 5 by
5 tile area) of the labyrinth is shown.

  You can move using the mouse or with the cursor keys of the
keyboard.

  Have fun!

